<h1>Carlos Puchol</h1>

<hr size=3>
<h2>Research Interests</h2>
<ul>
	<ul>
	<li><a href="http://cs-www.bu.edu/pub/ieee-rts/Home.html">Responsive/Real-time/Reactive Systems</a> in General
	<li><a href="http://www.comlab.ox.ac.uk/archive/formal-methods/">Formal Methods</a>
	<li>Specification and Implementation of Real-Time Systems
	<li>Distributed Control
	<li>Robotics
	<li><a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/cpg/TempEst">Esterel</a>, a synchronous programming language.
	<li><a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/cpg/mawl">Mawl</a>, a language for web applications development.
</ul>
</ul>

Check out the UTCS <a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/cpg/RTS/">Real-Time Systems Group</a> home page.

<hr size=3>

<h2>Publications</h2>

I have a list of <a href=http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/cpg/pub>publications</a> available for
browsing.<p>

<hr size=3>

<h2>Software</h2>

<a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/cpg/TempEst">The TempEst Toolset</a>: a package for verifying
safety properties of programs written in the <a
href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/cpg/TempEst/esterel.html">Esterel</a> programming language.

<p>

I once wrote one and a half Linux device drivers, one for the
<a href="ftp://sunsite.unc.edu/pub/Linux/apps/video/fgrabber-1.0.tgz">QuantaVision
frame grabber</a> and part of the
<a href="ftp://sunsite.unc.edu/pub/Linux/kernel/patches/console/joystick-0.7.3.tar.gz">joystick</a>
device driver.

